# Wellfit QA — prefer STAGE when adapting test docs

When Chris shares a **testing guide, runbook, Postman collection, or any doc** used to know how to test a ticket:

## Default

- **QA almost always tests in STAGE**, not DEV.
- If the artifact is **DEV-oriented** (DEV hosts, DEV identity, DEV Service Bus, DEV-only flags, “run on DEV first”, etc.), **adapt it for STAGE** before / while walking Chris through the test — do not leave him on DEV URLs by default.

## What to adjust

| Area | Action |
|------|--------|
| Base URLs / Azure app hosts | Map DEV → STAGE equivalents only when known/verified. If unsure of host or path → **ask Chris** (`wellfit-qa-ask-chris-before-guess.mdc`); do not invent unverified twins. |
| Identity / token | STAGE identity (`stage-wf-identity-api` or `stage-platform.wellfit.com/identity`) + STAGE clients from `wellfit-qa-stage-credentials.mdc`. |
| Postman env / variables | Prefer a **STAGE** environment file; hardcode or prefill STAGE values so QA does not fight placeholders. |
| Auth scopes / clients | Confirm the STAGE client actually has the required scope (DEV-proven client may still work on STAGE — verify; do not assume UnifiedPayments has Wrapper scopes). |
| Flags / feature gates | Note if a flag is OFF on STAGE or DEV-only; call out blockers for STAGE explicitly. |
| Synthetic inject / az / SB | If the guide says “only DEV can inject”, keep that caveat — do **not** pretend STAGE can do it; still adapt everything else that *can* run on STAGE. |

## How to deliver

- Update the ticket’s Postman/env/guide under `tickets/PAY-XXXX/` when adapting (or say clearly what Chris must change).
- In step-by-step walkthroughs with Chris: **default to STAGE steps**.
- If Part of the suite is DEV-only (parked E2E, flag, etc.), separate clearly: **STAGE runnable** vs **DEV-only / blocked**.

## Why

DEV-oriented Brett/dev runbooks cause QA friction (wrong hosts, secrets, scopes). STAGE config mismatches are a recurring blocker — prefer STAGE from the start.
